1.
    a.
        More cars would result in an increase in atmospheric carbon dioxide as ICE cars burn fuel to move, and combustion releases carbon dioxide; electric vehicles depend on energy from the grid which is predominantly powered via fossil fuels, the combustion of which also results in carbon dioxide being released into the air. Carbon dioxide being released into the atmosphere then leads to an increase in atmospheric carbon dioxide.
    b.
        Carbon dioxide is a greenhouse gas, which traps heat by reflecting heat radiation back into the earth, which increases the temperature of the earth and hence causes global warming.
    c.
        Because photosynthesis requires carbon dioxide, and so a higher carbon dioxide concentration means the concentration gradient between the atmosphere and the plant is higher, so carbon dioxide will diffuse at a higher rate into the leaf of the plant, and so more carbon dioxide will be available, so photosynthesis will happen faster.
    d.
        Because carbon sinks are ecosystem, and in an ecosystem there must be organisms that respire; e.g. plants also respire in order to release energy from glucose which is obtained via photosynthesis in order to grow, reproduce, and hence further photosynthesize; also, respiration releases carbon dioxide instead of taking it in, so the more respiration, the slower the rate at which the carbon sink takes up carbon dioxide; since plants are required to photosynthesize, and forests contain trees which make up a large portion of photosynthetic capability, deforestation reduces the amount of trees and forests and so means there will be less plants -> less (lower rate of) photosynthesis -> less carbon dioxide taken up.
    e.
        Taking a duckweed, place it fully submerged in water in a container. Place a lamp a set distance from the duckweed, and over a period of one minute, count the amount of bubbles released by the duckweed. Then, move the same lamp to a different distance (further -> lower light intensity, closer -> higher light intensity) and repeat this process. Then, repeat for all distances three times. Take the mean of n(gas bubbles in a minute) for each distance. This is the rate of gas exchange for that distance of lamp and hence light intensity.
    f.
        (150/((0.4/10)^2)) * 2
        = 187500
    g.
        Stomata opens to allow more gas flow through the leaf, which leads to a higher rate of water evaporation from the leaf, which lowers the water potential of the cells in the leaf, which creates a gradient of water potential from the root cells which have high water potential to the leaf cells which have a lower water potential, so water moves from the roots to the leaves via osmosis.
