    b.
        Cutting into six discs increases surface area of the potato, so hydrogen peroxide diffuses into the cells at a higher rate, so the reaction of hydrogen peroxide which is catalyzed by catalase will occur at a higher rate, so the teacher will not have to wait as long for the same results.
    c.
        i.
            total volume of gas collected after five minutes
        ii.
            Temperature of the hydrogen peroxide and the potato slices
            Concentration of hydrogen peroxide
    d.
        i.
            (2.4 - 0.8)/0.8 = 2 = 200%
        ii.
            Because as the hydrogen peroxide is used up, concentration of hydrogen peroxide decreases, so the collisions between hydrogen peroxide and catalase will become less frequent, so there will be less successful reactions per unit time, so the mean rate of reaction will decrease.
        iii?
            A pH that is too high or too low will lead to enzymes being denatured, changing the shape of their active site, and so no longer being able to catalyze the reaction, so rate of reaction will decrease as a result.
